						<summary>

						<p>Above the first three images, first row, on the Karuppannasami rock at Uttamapāḷaiyam,</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chaḍaiyamāṟan (Rājasimha II), Year 20 = 925 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>In Vaṭṭeḻuttu characters. Much damaged and refers to some Tīrttappaḷḷi, the Jaina temple, and Koṟkai in Kuḍa-nāḍu.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, XIV, No. 69.]</p>						

